SIMPLE: tidemark
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tidemark
<hw>Tide"mark</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a mark on a shore
line indicating the normal level of the water at high tide, caused by
the action of the flowing water; sometimes also used for the mark left
at the point of the normal low tide; -- called also <altname>high water
mark</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>the maximum level which some
activity has reached and from which it has declined; -- called also
<altname>high water mark</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tide-rode</ent>⟦br⟧
